{
  "texts": [
    "Articles were labeled using the Natural Language Processing (NLP) tool named Keyphrase Extraction to extract important phrases from each article, allowing us to label documents by reading only lists of words instead of whole web pages.",
    "We later built a binary text classifier using this dataset based on RoBERTa [7].In this paper, we present a pipeline that performs classification, clustering, labeling, and position tagging to address our third research goal.",
    "First, the classifier detects CT documents within any new datasets.",
    "Such documents are passed to a clustering algorithm.",
    "The user then labels and extracts named entities from each of the clusters, which provides us with insights into the new dataset."
  ]
}